Section 1:
1 L.D. 45
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 CRIMINAL JUSTICE AND PUBLIC SAFETY
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 9, L.D. 45, “An Act Allowing the
10 Department of Corrections to Offset Some of the Costs of Technology Provided to
11 Residents of Correctional Facilities”
12 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 2 and inserting the following:
13 'Sec. 2. 34-A MRSA §1403, sub-§14 is enacted to read:
14 14. Technology fee. The commissioner may establish a reasonable fee, as provided
15 in this subsection, for the use of technology, including, but not limited to, computers, laptop
16 computers and external storage devices, that is provided to residents of correctional
17 facilities in connection with educational or vocational programs, remote work or other
18 purposes. For each calendar month in which the technology is used by a resident, as defined
19 in section 3015, subsection 1, paragraph B, the fee charged may not exceed 7% of the
20 resident's earnings during the month after any deductions for court-ordered or statutory
21 obligations, including, but not limited to, child support, court filing fees, victim restitution,
22 fines, facility restitution, facility monetary sanctions, medical and dental services fees and
23 room and board, or $35, whichever is less. The commissioner may not charge a fee under
24 this subsection for:
25 A. Technology that is provided to a resident for the purpose of research related to a
26 criminal case or civil lawsuit in which the resident is involved; or
27 B. Technology that is provided to a resident who has earnings of less than $100 during
28 the calendar month after any deductions that are provided for in this subsection.
29 Money received by the resident and directly deposited into a telephone call account
30 established by the department under section 3039, subsection 4 for the sole purpose of
31 paying for use of the department's client telephone system is not subject to this subsection.
32 Money received by the resident as a credit improvement loan in accordance with section
33 3039, subsection 6 is not subject to this subsection.
34 A correctional facility shall collect any fees received under this subsection and deposit them
35 into the Resident Technology Fund established in section 1220.
