COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 9, L.D. 45
1 Sec. 3. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
2 allocations are made.
3 CORRECTIONS, DEPARTMENT OF
4 Resident Technology Fund N383
5 Initiative: Establishes the Resident Technology Fund.
6 OTHER SPECIAL REVENUE FUNDS 2025-26 2026-27
7 All Other $38,598 $38,598
8 __________ __________
9 OTHER SPECIAL REVENUE FUNDS TOTAL $38,598 $38,598
106 '
11 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
12 number to read consecutively.
13 SUMMARY
1144 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, amends the bill by
1155 providing financial limits on the proposed technology fee that the Commissioner of
1166 Corrections may impose by requiring that the fee may not exceed 7% of the resident's
1177 earnings for the calendar month after accounting for the specified deductions or $35,
1188 whichever is less. It also prohibits charging a technology fee to a resident who earns less
1199 than $100 in a month after any deductions are applied. The amendment clarifies that money
2200 received by a resident and directly deposited into a correctional facility telephone call
2211 account is not considered when calculating the resident's earnings. Money received by a
2222 resident as part of a credit improvement loan is also not considered when calculating the
2233 resident's earnings. The amendment also adds an appropriations and allocations section.
2244 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
2255 (See attached)
